parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Inadequate Seat Belt Length and Accessibility
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Inadequate seat belt length and accessibility can lead to difficulty or impossibility in properly restraining passengers, increasing the risk of injury or fatality in the event of an accident.
symptoms: buckle recessed too far into the seat cushion
female parts of the seat belt are too short
seat belts do not fit around the consumer
seat belts are hard to buckle due to placement
and seat belt receptacles are too short.
